      	<div class="page-title" style="margin:0;color:#f7c815;">PRODRIVER SERIES</div>
        <div style="font-size:1.2em; color:#fff; margin:10px 0 20px 0; line-height:20px;">ProDriver respects your privacy, and takes the responsibility of protecting the personal and business information that you provide to ProDriver  via the ProDriver website (the "Site"), very seriously. To that end ProDriver herein discloses its privacy practices and the possible uses of the information that it gathers via its Site. Please note that ProDriver may update this Privacy Policy from time-to-time at its sole discretion. It is your responsibility to review the Privacy Policy for any changes each time that you use the Site.</div>
        <div style="font-size:1.4em; font-weight:bold; color:#f7c815; margin:10px 0 0 0;">Information Collected and Used</div>
        <div style="font-size:1.2em; color:#fff; margin:10px 0 20px 0; line-height:20px;">In order to take part in ProDriver services, obtain information from ProDriver or have questions answered by ProDriver, ProDriver may request and/or collect personal information that may include, without limitation, your first and last name, home address, phone number, email address, drivers licenses, medical reports, social security number and other information needed to create a DOT certified driver qualification file (DQ). <br>
          <br>
        By entering Personal Information on the Site, you consent to our use of the Personal Information for purposes related to the Site and the services offered and/or provided on or in connection with the Site. This applies to the Fair Credit Reporting Act Section 604(b)(2)(a), public law 91-508 as it was amended by the CCRA of 1996, (title 2)(subtitle D)(Chapter 1) of( public law 104-208) you are being informed that reports verifying your previous employment, drug and alcohol test results and your driving records may be obtained for employment purposes. These reports are required by section 382.413 and 391.25 of the FMCSA. Without limiting the foregoing, by giving us Personal Information you are giving us permission to contact you and/or send you promotional and/or other marketing information about services and offerings from ProDriver. <br>
        <br>
        You have the right to review, correct and offer rebuttal to all information gathered by ProDriver as it pertains to our research. You also understand that by giving false and misleading information may result in loss of use to the Prodriver site as well as termination of work gained through this site.</div>
        <div style="font-size:1.4em; font-weight:bold; color:#f7c815; margin:10px 0 0 0;">Information Sharing</div>
        <div style="font-size:1.2em; color:#fff; margin:10px 0 20px 0; line-height:20px;">ProDriver will never sell or trade your personal identifying information. ProDriver collects information from its members in order to create a profile. ProDriver may share certain Personal Information collected within the Site in order to perform database searches with its prescreened company. Personal identifying information collected by ProDriver may be transferred as the sole responsibility of the members. ProDriver is not a PEO or job placement service and is not liable for transferred information. Personal Identifying information uploaded to the site is for storage and is only accessible by the member themselves. Members have to agree and perform the act of giving their DQ to the prescreened member company.</div>
        <div style="font-size:1.4em; font-weight:bold; color:#f7c815; margin:10px 0 0 0;">Security</div>
        <div style="font-size:1.2em; color:#fff; margin:10px 0 20px 0; line-height:20px;">ProDriver uses industry-standard security measures to protect certain Personal Information. However, no data transmitted over or accessible through the public Internet can be guaranteed to be 100% secure. As a result, while we attempt to protect Personal Information, ProDriver cannot ensure or warrant that Personal Information will be completely secure from misappropriation by hackers or from other nefarious or criminal activities, or in the event of a failure of computer hardware, software, or a telecommunications network. At this time no personal information is stored on static servers, cloud servers or other shared ISP equipment. The transfer of information is stored as hard copy files until time of request by a verified user. Files are transmitted digitally to the user with permission of the driver at the time of request.</div>
